### Issue

- **What did you do?**
I'm trying to convert my ML code in python using scikit-learn to C# using ML.NET
- **What happened?**
I noticed that the result with robust scaling in the pipeline using ML.NET did not match the results from python. The difference seems to be due to a different 'scale' value and the used function.
- **What did you expect?**
I have checked  the scale and offset of the data in EXCEL using the QUARTILE.INC() function and these results suggest that the values from python are correct. 
I've also derived from the [documentation ](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/api/microsoft.ml.transforms.normalizingtransformer.affinenormalizermodelparameters-1?view=ml-dotnet#properties) that ML.NET seems to use the `(input - offset) * scale` function to calculate the normalized value while the python code uses `(input - offset) \ scale`

- I would like to know why this result is so different and whether this is bug or not.

Below you can find an example code to demonstrate the difference
### Source code C#
```
private class TestInput
{
	[ColumnName(@"Test")]
	public float Test { get; set; }
}

[TestMethod]
public void NormalizedTest()
{
	List<TestInput> testInputs = new List<TestInput>()
	{
		new TestInput(){Test = 2.114265f },
		new TestInput(){Test = 2.837738f },
		new TestInput(){Test = 2.909677f },
		new TestInput(){Test = 3.769787f },
	};

	var mlContext = new MLContext();
	IDataView dataView = mlContext.Data.LoadFromEnumerable<TestInput>(testInputs);

	//normalize
	var normalize = mlContext.Transforms.NormalizeRobustScaling(new[] {
			new InputOutputColumnPair(@"Test", @"Test") });
	var normalizeTransform = normalize.Fit(dataView);
	var transformedData = normalizeTransform.Transform(dataView);
	var affineParams = normalizeTransform.GetNormalizerModelParameters(0) as AffineNormalizerModelParameters<float>;
	var offset = affineParams.Offset;
	var scale = affineParams.Scale;
	Console.WriteLine($"Offset: {offset}");
	Console.WriteLine($"Scale: {scale}");
	List<TestInput> vals = mlContext.Data.CreateEnumerable<TestInput>(
	transformedData, reuseRowObject: false).ToList();
	for (int i = 0; i < vals.Count; i++) {
		//y = (x - ({ offset})) * { scale}
		Console.WriteLine($"{(testInputs[i].Test - offset) * scale} \t  {vals[i].Test}");
	}
}
```

